    <item>
      <title>Which groups do users belong to? A Graph API approach</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/get-mgusermemberof/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 23 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/get-mgusermemberof/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;whats-that&#34;&gt;What&amp;rsquo;s that?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Just another script for listing users and their group memberships.
You feed it a text file with UPNs, it queries Microsoft Graph, and spits out a flat CSV like:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;table&gt;
  &lt;thead&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;th&gt;UserPrincipalName&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th&gt;PrimarySmtpAddress&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th&gt;GroupName&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th&gt;GroupEmail&lt;/th&gt;
          &lt;th&gt;GroupType&lt;/th&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/thead&gt;
  &lt;tbody&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:user1@company.com&#34;&gt;user1@company.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:user1@company.com&#34;&gt;user1@company.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Some Distribution List&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:some-dl@company.com&#34;&gt;some-dl@company.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;DistributionList&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:user1@company.com&#34;&gt;user1@company.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:user1@company.com&#34;&gt;user1@company.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Security Group ABC&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:sg-abc@company.com&#34;&gt;sg-abc@company.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;MailSecurityGroup&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
      &lt;tr&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:user2@company.com&#34;&gt;user2@company.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:user2@company.com&#34;&gt;user2@company.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;Some Distribution List&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;mailto:some-dl@company.com&#34;&gt;some-dl@company.com&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
          &lt;td&gt;DistributionList&lt;/td&gt;
      &lt;/tr&gt;
  &lt;/tbody&gt;
&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;wheres-it&#34;&gt;Where&amp;rsquo;s it?&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://github.com/przemekokon/Staff-from-blog/blob/main/Get-MgUserMemberOf.ps1&#34;&gt;On GitHub&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h2 id=&#34;requirements&#34;&gt;Requirements&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PowerShell 5.1+ or PowerShell 7+&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Microsoft Graph PowerShell SDK&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Permissions: &lt;code&gt;User.Read.All&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;GroupMember.Read.All&lt;/code&gt;, &lt;code&gt;Group.Read.All&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>How to Update Proxy Addresses for a Cloud-Only Object</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/proxy_removal_graph/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 16 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/proxy_removal_graph/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;problem&#34;&gt;Problem&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to add or remove (basically update) a proxy address on a cloud-only account - without an Exchange mailbox - you cannot.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;There is no such option in the GUI and PowerShell won&amp;rsquo;t allow it either, throwing an error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;Set-MgUser : Property &amp;#39;proxyAddresses&amp;#39; is read-only and cannot be set.
Status: 400 (BadRequest)
ErrorCode: Request_BadRequest
&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;h2 id=&#34;solution&#34;&gt;Solution&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Use the Graph API &lt;strong&gt;BETA&lt;/strong&gt; endpoint.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Method:&lt;/strong&gt; PATCH&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;URL:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;https://graph.microsoft.com/beta/users/&amp;lt;User_ID&amp;gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Request Body:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;div class=&#34;highlight&#34;&gt;&lt;div class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;
&lt;table class=&#34;lntable&#34;&gt;&lt;tr&gt;&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;1
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;2
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;3
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;4
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;5
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;6
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;7
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;lnt&#34;&gt;8
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;
&lt;td class=&#34;lntd&#34;&gt;
&lt;pre tabindex=&#34;0&#34; class=&#34;chroma&#34;&gt;&lt;code class=&#34;language-json&#34; data-lang=&#34;json&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;{&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;nt&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;proxyAddresses&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;:&lt;/span&gt; &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;[&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;SMTP:PrimarySMTPAddress&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;smtp:Alias1&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;smtp:Alias2&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;,&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;        &lt;span class=&#34;s2&#34;&gt;&amp;#34;smtp:Alias3&amp;#34;&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;    &lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;]&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;line&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;cl&#34;&gt;&lt;span class=&#34;p&#34;&gt;}&lt;/span&gt;
&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;&lt;/td&gt;&lt;/tr&gt;&lt;/table&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Expected Response:&lt;/strong&gt; &lt;code&gt;204 No Content&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;figure&gt;
    &lt;img loading=&#34;lazy&#34; src=&#34;http://localhost:1313/images/proxy_update.png&#34;
         alt=&#34;Graph Explorer&#34;/&gt; &lt;figcaption&gt;
            &lt;p&gt;An example&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
    <item>
      <title>Search Tenant Objects by Domain</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/posts/search-tenant-by-domain/</link>
      <pubDate>Mon, 16 Mar 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/posts/search-tenant-by-domain/</guid>
      <description>&lt;h2 id=&#34;domain-removal-issues&#34;&gt;Domain Removal Issues&lt;/h2&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If you want to remove a domain from an M365 tenant, you need to deprovision all associated objects first - easy to say, harder to do.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the domain is not federated, M365 can handle it for you - it simply removes aliases and updates the Primary SMTP address and/or UPN to the default domain (domain.onmicrosoft.com).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;However, this does not work for federated domains. You have to remove everything manually, which is manageable for one domain. In my case, I had to remove 150.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
    </item>
